## Quick Reference {#sec-stan-quick-ref}

| Problem observed | Technique | Section |
|---|---|---|
| Redundant computation during leapfrog | Block placement → `transformed data` | [§1](#sec-block-placement) |
| Quantity derived from data only, easier to compute in R | Pre-compute in R | [§2](#sec-precompute-r) |
| Many IID trials, one parameter per session | Sufficient statistics → `binomial_lpmf` | [§3](#sec-sufficient-stats) |
| Trial loop over identical distribution | Vectorize the likelihood call | [§4](#sec-vectorize) |
| Changing priors requires recompiling | Priors as data | [§5](#sec-priors-as-data) |
| SBC / LOO is slow | `run_diagnostics` flag | [§6](#sec-run-diagnostics) |
| Want PPC/LOO without re-running MCMC | `$generate_quantities()` post-hoc | [§7](#sec-generate-quantities) |
| Divergences / low E-BFMI in multilevel model | Non-centered parameterization (NCP) | [§8](#sec-ncp) |
| Simplex + small kappa → funnel geometry | Logit-normal NCP for simplex | [§8](#sec-ncp) |
| Model has correlation matrix $\Omega$ | Cholesky factorization (`lkj_corr_cholesky`) | [§9](#sec-cholesky) |
| Sequential model with per-subject trial loops | Contiguous `subj_start`/`subj_end` indexing | [§10](#sec-subject-indexing) |
| Slow warm-up on complex / hierarchical model | Pathfinder warm-start | [§11](#sec-pathfinder) |
| Discrete latent variables (indicators, regimes) | Marginalise with `log_mix` | [§12](#sec-log-mix) |
| Trial-to-trial latent state in likelihood | Sequential unrolling in `transformed parameters` | [§13](#sec-sequential-state) |
| Many subjects, multi-core machine | `reduce_sum` intra-chain parallelism | [§14](#sec-reduce-sum) |
| Divergences / treedepth / slow warm-up | Sampler options (`adapt_delta`, `max_treedepth`) | [§16](#sec-sampler-options) |
| Slow compilation or runtime on algebraic models | Compiler flags (`-O3 -march=native`) | [§16](#sec-sampler-options) |
| Large `.csv` output files | Reduce `sig_figs` to 6 | [§16](#sec-sampler-options) |
